==Spanish==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[super]]'', '''above'''
===Preposition===
'''sobre'''
# [[over]], [[above]], [[on]]
#: ''La pluma de mi t&iacute;a est&aacute; sobre la mesa.'' My aunt's pen is on the table.
# [[about]]
#: ''Dime algo sobre ti.'' Tell me something about yourself.

====Usage note====
''Sobre'' is slightly informal. In the sense of ''over'' or ''on'', it is often replaced in formal contexts with the more general ''[[en#Spanish|en]]'', or with the more verbose ''[[arriba]] [[de#Spanish|de]]'' or ''[[encima]] de''. In the sense of ''about'', it is usually replaced in formal contexts with ''[[acerca]] de'', or simply ''de'' if the context is sufficient to make the meaning clear.

